olive oil
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet ginger paste
1 packet beef strips
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 tbs soy sauce
1 tin sweetcorn
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 carrot
1 bag super slaw
1 bunch spring onion
1 drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)

• Drain the sweetcorn. Grate the carrot.
• Discard any liquid from beef strips packaging.

• When oil is hot, cook ginger paste and beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Return all beef to the pan, then add sweet chilli sauce and the soy sauce and cook until reduced, 1 minute.

• Meanwhile, combine super slaw, carrot, sweetcorn, mayonnaise and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil in a large bowl. Season to taste.
• Thinly slice spring onion.

• Divide slaw between bowls.
• Top with sweet chilli-ginger beef, spooning over any remaining sauce from the pan.
• Sprinkle with crispy shallots and spring onion to serve. Enjoy!